Moreover, the Fact laid down, that the Veins are pre-
ternaturally diſtended with Blood, does neceſſarily con-
clude, that the Arteries are not diſtended with it, and
conſequently that there cannot be any Inflammation;
for if the Quantity of Blood is encreaſed in the Veins,
it muſt be proportionably diminiſhed in the Arteries.
